<Docs title="Deployment" description="Environment variables and secrets for Dep Beacon deployment.">
  <h1>Deployment</h1>
  <p>
    Copy `.env.example` to `.env` for local commands. In GitHub, add the same values as repository secrets or variables as noted below.
  </p>

  <h2>Required GitHub secrets</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>`NPM_TOKEN` publishes `@santi020k/dep-beacon-core` to npm.</li>
    <li>`VSCE_PAT` publishes the packaged VSIX to Visual Studio Marketplace.</li>
    <li>`OVSX_PAT` publishes the same VSIX to Open VSX.</li>
    <li>`CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` deploys the docs build to Cloudflare Pages.</li>
    <li>`CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID` selects the Cloudflare account.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Optional GitHub variables</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>`CLOUDFLARE_PAGES_PROJECT_NAME` overrides the default `dep-beacon-docs` Pages project.</li>
    <li>`TURBO_TEAM` and `TURBO_TOKEN` enable Turbo remote caching when configured as secrets.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Local publishing checks</h2>
  <pre><code>pnpm run validate
pnpm --filter vscode-dep-beacon package</code></pre>

  <p>
    Publishing uses one built VSIX for both registries and passes duplicate-safe flags where the registries support them.
  </p>
</Docs>
